text: Arthyde is an unincorporated community in Aitkin County, Minnesota. Arthyde was previously known as Millward. In 1909, it was renamed to honor the names of two pioneer brothers, Arthur (1876-1960) and Clyde Hutchins (1878-1950). The Arthyde Stone House, built around 1922, is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
